import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="key", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Key', ylabel='Count')
    plt.title("What is the range of values for the 'key' field in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='key', data=data, palette='Set2')
    ax.set_title("What is the frequency of occurrence of each 'key' value in the dataset?")
    ax.set_xlabel('Key')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate('{:.2f}%'.format(100*p.get_height()/len(data)), (p.get_x()+0.3, p.get_height()+5))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="key", y="lat", data=data, ax=ax, ci=None)
    plt.title("What is the average latitude value for each 'key' value in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Key")
    plt.ylabel("Average Latitude")
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
